      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:5:3:39:2",
      "text": [
        " لَا بَأْسَ بِأَنْ يَنْظُرَ إِلَى وَجْهِهَا وَ مَعَاصِمِهَا إِذَا أَرَادَ أَنْ يَتَزَوَّجَهَا ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "From him, from his father, from Ibn Abu Umeyr, from Hisham Bin Salim, and Hammad Bin Usman and Hafs Bin Al Bakhtary, all of them, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> having said: ‘There is no problem with looking at her face and her two wrists when you intend to marry her’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "2. It is narrated from the narrator of the previous Hadith from ibn abu ‘Umayr from Hisham ibn Salim and Hammad ibn ‘Uthman and Hafs ibn al-Bakhtariy all have said the following: “Abu ‘Abd Allah, ‘Alayhi al-Salam, has said, ‘It is not unlawful for a man to look at her face and hands to wrists, if he wants to marry her.’” "
        ]
      }
